 To implement the thermal equilibriation in Ehrenfest+R method, we use the
 same mechanism to rescale the wave function.
 The population change is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
d\rho=dt\gamma\left(e^{-\beta\varepsilon_{1}}\left|c_{0}\right|^{2}-e^{-\beta\varepsilon_{0}}\left|c_{1}\right|^{2}\right)
\end{equation}

\end_inset

and the wave function is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
c_{0}^{\prime}\rightarrow c_{0}^{\prime\prime}=\frac{c_{0}^{\prime}}{\left|c_{0}^{\prime}\right|}\sqrt{\left|c_{0}^{\prime}\right|^{2}-d\rho}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
